  "Dogs on the Run": `yeah when the leaves had died and all turned black back when the wind was cold and blew them around when we laid our blankets on the ground yeah and i woke up feeling hungry looking straight into the sun and left a cold night on the ground like a dog on the run i fell overboard and washed up on a beach let waves and sand roll over me i was helped to the home of a young bleached blonde who said honey i discovered early in life theres ways of getting anything i want some of us are different its just something in our blood theres no need for explanations were just dogs on the run its just dogs on the run yes the room was painted blue and grey all my meals came to me on a silver tray yeah she would laugh and light my cigarettes she said honey aint it funny how a crowd gathers around anyone living life without a net yea how theyll beg you for the answer but it wont ever be enough theres no way you could ever tell em its just dogs on the run its just dogs on the run its just dogs on the run babe like a dog on the run like a dog on the run like a dog like a dog like a dog on the run yeah`,
